# Prisma Patterns

## Required patterns
- Access database through `PrismaService` injected by NestJS DI.
- Keep data access in service layer; controllers should stay thin.
- Use Prisma model types and DTO mapping instead of loose object shapes.

## Forbidden patterns
- Do not use raw SQL (`$queryRaw`, `$executeRaw`) unless explicitly required and justified.
- Do not introduce any other ORM in backend modules.
- Do not perform database writes directly in controllers.

## Schema and migration workflow
- Any schema change must be followed by migration and Prisma client generation.
- Keep schema changes minimal and backward compatible when possible.
- Document non-trivial migration impact in PR notes.
